    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AdminHomePage
    AdminHomePage provides the administrative user interface for managing users and performing tasks such as inviting new users, viewing reviewer requests, modifying user roles, banning/unbanning users, and generating one-time passwords.
    AdminRequests
    Provides an administrative interface for managing user-submitted requests.
    AdminSetupPage
    The AdminSetupPage class handles the setup process for creating an administrator account.
    Answer
    Represents an answer in the system.
    AskToBeAReviewer
    This class handles the page where the student can request to become a reviewer
    CreateMessagePage
    Page where a user can create and send a new message.

    Title: DatabaseHelper Class.

    Title: PasswordEvaluationTestingAutomation Class.
    EmailValidator
    The EmailValidator class provides methods to validate email addresses using a Finite State Machine (FSM) approach.
    FindReviewerForQuestionPage
    The FindReviewerForQuestionPage class provides a JavaFX-based user interface for finding and assigning reviewers for questions.
    Inbox
    The Inbox class displays the Inbox view for a user.
    InstructorHomePage
    InstructorHomePage is responsible for displaying the instructor's home page interface.
    InstructorRequest
    The InstructorRequest class is responsible for displaying all user-submitted requests to the instructor in a tabular format using JavaFX.
    InstructorReviewerRequest
    Handles the display and management of reviewer requests submitted by instructors.
    InvitationPage
    InvitePage class represents the page where an admin can generate an invitation code.
    Message
    Represents a message exchanged between users in the system.
    MessageTestingAutomation
    MessageTestingAutomation is a console-based test runner used to validate the message creation and insertion functionality of the message database.
    NameEvaluationTestingAutomation
    Title: PasswordEvaluationTestingAutomation Class.
    NameValidator
    The NameValidator class provides functionality to validate names using a Finite State Machine (FSM) approach.
    NewPasswordPage
    The NewPasswordPage class provides a user interface for resetting a user's password.
    PasswordEvaluationTestingAutomation
    Title: PasswordEvaluationTestingAutomation Class.
    PasswordEvaluator
    The PasswordEvaluator class provides functionality to validate a password using a finite state machine (FSM) approach implemented as a directed graph.

    Enum representing the type of row.
    Question
    Represents a question posted by a user along with its metadata.
    QuestionAndAnswerAutomation
    This class automates the testing of Question and Answer functionalities using a database connection.

    The ReadMessagePage class displays the details of a specific message, including the sender, subject, reference information, and message content.
